  "prompt": "What do you do if you run out of underwear and money?",
  "response": "If you find yourself out of underwear and short on money, here are a few strategies you could consider:\n\n1. **Hand-Washing Existing Underwear**: You can wash your existing underwear by hand using soap and water. This can make them last longer between laundry cycles.\n\n2. **Repurposing Other Clothing**: You could use other clothing items, such as shorts or even old t-shirts, as makeshift underwear.\n\n3. **Thrift Stores**: Check local thrift stores for affordable options. Sometimes you can find gently-used underwear at very low prices.\n\n4. **DIY Solutions**: If you have fabric and some basic sewing skills, you could try making your own underwear.\n\n5. **Community Support**: Reach out to local charities or support organizations that may provide clothing assistance. Places like shelters, churches, and community centers often have programs to help those in need.\n\n6. **Borrowing**: If you're comfortable, you could ask close friends or family members if they have any spare underwear.\n\n7. **Sales and Discounts**: Look for sales, discounts, and clearance items at stores. Sometimes you can find underwear at significantly reduced prices.\n\n8. **Budgeting and Saving**: Plan to set aside a small amount from any future income for essential clothing needs.\n\nRemember to always prioritize hygiene and find the safest and most comfortable solutions for your situation.",
